Powershell is a nice language.<p>Here&#x27;s map/filter/reduce. Golf welcome.<p><pre><code>  @(1, 2, 3) `
     | % { $_ + 1 } `
     | ? { $_ -gt 2 } `
     | Measure-Object -Sum
     | Select Sum
</code></pre>
You can write a generic reduce like this:<p><pre><code>  $reduce = {
    param   ([scriptblock]$reducer)
    begin   { $initialised = $false }
    process { 
      if (-not $initialised) {
        $agg = $_
        $initialised = $true
      } else {
        $agg = &$reducer $agg $_
      }
    }
    end     { $agg }
  }
</code></pre>
And then use it like this:<p><pre><code>  @(1, 2, 3) | &$reduce { param($agg, $i) $agg + $i }</code></pre>
